Reasoning: The paper deals with emergent language simulations with neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also discusses the training of neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL). The paper's focus on the basic properties of the induced code and how they compare to human language suggests that it could also fall under the category of computational linguistics (CL). Finally, the paper's analysis of the functional pressures that lead to successful communication codes suggests that it could also fall under the category of systems and control (SD).
